Introduction

Hwang Mi-young, popularly known as Tiffany Young, is a South Korean-American singer-songwriter, composer, and actress under SUBLIME, Transparent Arts, and Paradigm Talent Agency. She is best known as one of the lead vocalists of the girl group Girls' Generation which debuted in 2007. She is also the main rapper and lead vocalist of the group's sub-unit Girls' Generation-TTS alongside with members Taeyeon and Seohyun.

Tiffany made her solo debut on May 11, 2016, with the mini-album "I Just Wanna Dance." Since she departed from SM Entertainment in October 2017, she has been releasing music under the stage name Tiffany Young.
